  "identified_domain": "adventure_works",
  "domain_research_summary": "Extensive industry research and Kyvos documentation review confirms that AdventureWorks is a canonical example for enterprise BI \u2014 specifically for a bike manufacturing and retail company with internet and reseller sales channels, finance, and HR analytics. Standard modeling is a multifact schema aligning fact tables by sales channel and financial reporting, with conformed dimensions for product, customer, promotion, territory, currency, channel, and rich time intelligence via a calendar/date table. Parent-child hierarchies for employee, organization, and account enable organizational analyses. Bridge/junction tables capture many-to-many relationships (e.g., sales_reasons). KPIs must use MDX syntax for time intelligence (YTD, QTD, MTD, ParallelPeriod) and safe division. Hierarchies must use actual schema columns per best practices. Kyvos documentation (MDX Functions Guide, hierarchy/rollup best practices) is referenced throughout the design.",
